{"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"PowerProfileMonitorRef"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"level":2,"text":"Overview","type":"heading","anchor":"overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"When in “Low Power” mode, it is recommended that applications:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"disable automatic downloads;"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"reduce the rate of refresh from online sources such as calendar or","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"email synchronisation;","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"reduce the use of expensive visual effects."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It is also likely that OS components providing services to applications will"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"lower their own background activity, for the sake of the system.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"There are a variety of tools that exist for power consumption analysis, but those","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"usually depend on the OS and hardware used. On Linux, one could use "},{"code":"upower","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"monitor the battery discharge rate, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"powertop"},{"type":"text","text":" to check on the background activity"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"or activity at all), ","type":"text"},{"code":"sysprof","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to inspect CPU usage, and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"intel_gpu_time"},{"text":" to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"profile GPU usage."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Don’t forget to disconnect the [signal[Object](\/\/documentation\/gobject\/object\/onnotify(flags:handler:)] signal for","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[property"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/PowerProfileMonitor","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"], and unref the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GPowerProfileMonitor"},{"type":"text","text":" itself when exiting."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/PowerProfileMonitorRef"},{"type":"text","text":" type acts as a lightweight Swift reference to an underlying "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GPowerProfileMonitor"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"It exposes methods that can operate on this data type through "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/PowerProfileMonitorProtocol"},{"text":" conformance.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/PowerProfileMonitorRef","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" only as an "},{"code":"unowned","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" reference to an existing ","type":"text"},{"code":"GPowerProfileMonitor","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Use ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/PowerProfileMonitor","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" (instead of "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/PowerProfileMonitorRef"},{"text":") if you want to use Automatic Reference Counting for memory management of the underlying ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GPowerProfileMonitor"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"type":"aside","name":"Note","style":"note"}],"kind":"content"}],"sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO"]]},"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GPowerProfileMonitor"},{"text":" makes it possible for applications as well as OS","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"components to monitor system power profiles and act upon them. It currently","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"only exports whether the system is in “Power Saver” mode (known as","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"“Low Power” mode on some systems)."}],"topicSections":[{"title":"Initializers","generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/PowerProfileMonitorRef\/init(_:)-11ce","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/PowerProfileMonitorRef\/init(_:)-1lc7t","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/PowerProfileMonitorRef\/init(_:)-22ftz","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/PowerProfileMonitorRef\/init(_:)-4genn","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/PowerProfileMonitorRef\/init(_:)-7j8br","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/PowerProfileMonitorRef\/init(cPointer:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/PowerProfileMonitorRef\/init(constPointer:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/PowerProfileMonitorRef\/init(gconstpointer:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/PowerProfileMonitorRef\/init(gpointer:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/PowerProfileMonitorRef\/init(mutating:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/PowerProfileMonitorRef\/init(opaquePointer:)"],"anchor":"Initializers"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/PowerProfileMonitorRef\/ptr"],"generated":true,"title":"Instance Properties","anchor":"Instance-Properties"},{"generated":true,"title":"Type Methods","anchor":"Type-Methods","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/PowerProfileMonitorRef\/dupDefault()"]},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Po